  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Expositor's Greek Testament",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Matthew 10:7",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "πορευόμενοι κηρύσσετε",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", as ye go, keep preaching; participle and finite verb, both present. Preaching first in the Master’s thoughts, if not in the evangelist’s (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Matthew 10:1",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ").—",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "ἤγγικεν ἡ βασιλεία τ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "ο",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ".: the theme is, of course, the kingdom longed for by all, constantly on the lips of Jesus. The message is: It has come nigh to you and is here. Very general, but much more, it may be taken for granted, was said. The apprentice apostles could as yet make no intelligent theoretic statement concerning the ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Kingdom",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", but they could tell not a little about the ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "King",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", the Master who sent them, the chief object of interest doubtless for all receptive souls. It was a ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "house",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " mission (not in synagogue) on which they were sent (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Matthew 10:12",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). They were to live as guests in selected dwellings, two in one, and two in another, for a time, and their preaching would take the form of familiar conversation on what they had seen and heard Jesus do and say. They would talk by the hour, healing acts would be very occasional, one or two in a village.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Bengel's Gnomen",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Matthew 10:7",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "Πορευόμενοι",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "as ye go",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") Answering to ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "πορεύεσθε",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
